</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="chat_206.sea.hqx"><B>chat_206.sea.hqx</B></a>
<DD>TCP/IP Internet chat program for Mac. This is not IRC,
    but a new net.tool for wired Macintosh users. Binhex'd
    Self-Extracting Archive.
<DT><a href="eudora_dox.sea.hqx"><B>eudora_dox.sea.hqx</B></a>
<DD>Great self-displaying documentation for the Mac Eudora
    Internet email program. Binhex'd Self-Extracting Archive.
<DT><a href="ez-xfer_220.sea.hqx"><B>ez-xfer_220.sea.hqx</B></a>
<DD>Easy Transfer, a new Mac-only Internet file transfer
    protocol (avoids the need for BinHexing, splitting
    files, converting to MacBinary, translating line
    endings, etc.) Now supported by some Mac FTP sites!
    Binhex'd Self-Extracting Archive.
<DT><a href="mac_mosaic.faq"><B>mac_mosaic.faq</B></a>
<DD>Frequently Asked Questions and answers about NCSA Mosaic
    WWW browser for the Macintosh.
<DT><a href="mactcp.intro"><B>mactcp.intro</B></a>
<DD>Frequently Asked Questions and answers about MacTCP (Mac
    Internet packet driver, required for Mac use of the Internet.)
<DT><a href="telnet2.5docs.sit.hqx"><B>telnet2.5docs.sit.hqx</B></a>
<DD>NCSA Mac Telnet 2.5 documentation. BinHex'd StuffIt
    archive.
<DT><a href="telnet2.6bdocs.msw.sit.hqx"><B>telnet2.6bdocs.msw.sit.hqx</B></a>
<DD>NCSA Mac Telnet 2.6b documentation. BinHex'd
    StuffIt archive.
<DT><a href="tftpd_100.sea.hqx"><B>tftpd_100.sea.hqx</B></a>
<DD>TFTP (Trivial File Transfer Protocol - not to be
    confused with FTP at all, at all) server for Mac admins.
    TFTP is mainly used for transfer of control information
    and other routine tasks, and isn't really intended (or
    much good) for file transfers in the usual sense.
<DT><a href="tpc_convert_1.0d1.sea.hqx"><B>tpc_convert_1.0d1.sea.hqx</B></a>
<DD>Mac util to make tcp.int fax-via-internet easier
    BinHex'd Self-Extracting Archive. See /pub/
    Net_info/Technical/net-fax.* for info.
</DL>

