<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/earth2_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Links to Related Off-Site Resources</h2>
<DL>

<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.catalaw.com">CataLaw</A></B>
<DD> "The most efficient tool for finding law on the Internet."  CATALAW is the 
catalog of catalogs of law on the Internet. It speeds research by 
arranging hundreds of legal and government indexes into a single, 
simple, intuitive metaindex.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.batnet.com/oikoumene/">The WWW Multimedia Law 
Site</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="gopher://ba.com:70/11/Legal_Issues">Bell Atlantic Legal
    Issues</A> Gopher Archive</B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.lcp.com/The-Legal-List/TLL-home.html">The Legal
List</A>: Index of law-related resources on the Internet (HTML edition)</B>
<DT><B>GSU Law College <A 
HREF="http://www.gsu.edu/~lawadmn/gsulaw.html">Index
    of Law-Related Resources</A> on the World Wide Web</B>
<DT><B><a href="http://www.wired.com/Staff/justin/dox/law.html">Legal 
Beat</a></B>
<DT><B>Brad Cox's <A
HREF="http://gopher.gmu.edu/bcox/ElectronicFrontier/LawEthicsSociety.LaMacchia.html">
Law, Ethics, and Society on the Information Superhighway</A> Archive</B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.kentlaw.edu/lawnet/lawlinks.html">Chicago-Kent Law
School's Law Links Page</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.inter-law.com/">The 'Lectric Law Library</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.ljx.com"><I>Law Journal Extra!</I></A></B>
<DT><B>FullMoon Multi-Media's <A
HREF="http://fmmi.com/fullmoon/marketing/legal.html">Legal Issues &
Policy Pages</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.automatrix.com/~bak/real2.html">Book by Barry
Krusch:</A> <I>Would the Real First Amendment Please Stand Up?</I></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.gdf.com/lbytes.htm">Legal Bytes</A> Newsletter</B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.cybersquirrel.com/clc/">Cyberspace Law 
Center</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://lawlinks.com/forum.html">LawLinks Forum</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://vmag.law.vill.edu">Villanova Law School Center for 
Information Law &amp; Policy</A></B>
<DD>Provides links to virtual arbitration experiment, government info 
locators, & other legal resources.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.cli.org/">Cyberspace Law Institute</A></B>
<DD> studies, and helps to develop, the new
   forms of law and law-making required by the growth of global
   communications networks and online communities.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.cli.org/sysopl/sysopl.html">A Short Course
on Sysop Liability</A></B>
<DD>by the Cyberspace Law Institute
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/cyberspace/">A virtual "Course on 
Cyberspace Law for Non-Lawyers"</A></B>
<DD>by Profs. Larry Lessig, David Post, and Eugene Volokh.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.e-legal.com/">Electronic Legal Source</A></B>
<DD>This library is stocked with free legal forms and information
for both the general public and legal practitioners. You'll find
legal news, dictionaries, research links and directories of law
firms/schools. A small portion of the MANY free forms online include:
Proof of Service by Mail; Answer to Worker's Compensation Petition;
Loan Agreement; General Contractor's Agreement, and our personal
favorite, a Web Site Design, Storage, and Promotion Agreement.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.barcouncil.com">LIBS</A></B>
<DD>"The Latest Information for Barristers & Solicitors" - project which 
aims to be an extensive and in-depth site
covering all aspects of United Kingdom and Commonwealth law.  There is 
also a wide International section.
</DL>

