<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="18usc_s875c.law"><B>18usc_s875c.law</B></a>
<DD>law against transmission of threats; used in the Jake
    Baker case to attempt to prosecute Baker for the posting and emailing of
    violent sex fantasies and messages which discussed kidnapping and
    rape in a positive light.
<DT><a href="baker.story"><B>baker.story</B></a>
<DD>the original story authored by Jake Baker, which resulted in
    controversy, suspension, arrest and charges that were eventually dropped.
    WARNING: This evidentiary item, presented as part of the record of a
    legal case, contains, like many other items from sexual-violence-related
    cases, material that is of a sexually explicit and disturbing nature.
    Those who are not 18 years of age or older, and those who do not wish to
    be exposed to such materials, are warned to not download this file. We
    accept no responsibility for your failure to protect yourself from
    material you do not wish to see, nor for the failure of parents to
    supervise their own children's online activities. The presence of this
    item in these archives is protected by the First Amendment to the
    Constititution, because the file has clear merit as part of an education
    and research library.
<DT><a href="baker.timeline"><B>baker.timeline</B></a>
<DD>Brief description of the Baker case and a timeline of events
    from the posting of the article to the trial.
<DT><a href="baker_arrest_branam.article"><B>baker_arrest_branam.article</B></a>
<DD>article by Judson Branam regarding
    the Baker case. This dealt with Baker's posting of a story on a Usenet
    that contained a rape and death fantasy of a student of the University
    of Michigan. Article discusses baker's arrest by the FBI.
<DT><a href="baker_arrest_white_021095.article"><B>baker_arrest_white_021095.article</B></a>
<DD>another artice on Jake Baker's arrest 
    by the FBI.
<DT><a href="baker_barred_from_campus_020795.article"><B>baker_barred_from_campus_020795.article</B></a>
<DD>article about how Baker was 
    banned from campus, and not permitted to attend classes, despite the fact 
    that not court or campus hearings had found him guilty of anyhting.
<DT><a href="baker_bond_denied.article"><B>baker_bond_denied.article</B></a>
<DD>short article on Baker's being denied bond.
<DT><a href="baker_charges_dismissed.article"><B>baker_charges_dismissed.article</B></a>
<DD>article telling of the charges of Jake
    Baker being dismissed on the grounds that there was no intent to carry
    out the threats depicted in his story, and due to freedom of speech.
<DT><a href="baker_plea.article"><B>baker_plea.article</B></a>
<DD>short newsbyte on Baker entering a plea of not guilty.
<DT><a href="baker_scandal_miller.article"><B>baker_scandal_miller.article</B></a>
<DD>Article by Adam Miller describing the case
    of Jake Baker and the situation that led up to his arrest and trial.
<DT><a href="baker_umich_case.notes"><B>baker_umich_case.notes</B></a>
<DD>Summary of the behavior of the University
    of Michigan in response to Jake Baker's posting of a 'snuff' story
    on a usenet, and how they violated his civil liberties.
<DT><a href="da_green_baker_charges.announce"><B>da_green_baker_charges.announce</B></a>
<DD>Announcement by the U.S. Attorney
    Saul Green of the charges to be brought against Jake Baker for his
    explicit 'snuff' story on the usenet.
</DL>

