<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>EFF &quot;Legal Cases - FCC v Pacifica (George Carlin `7 Dirty Words` Case)&quot; Archive</TITLE><LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:webmaster@eff.org"></HEAD><BODY>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<H1><TD><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/">EFFWeb Welcome Page</A></TD></H1>
<H1><TD><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/">Alerts</A></TD></H1>
<H1><TD><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/links.html">Archive Index</A></TD></H1>
</TR></TABLE>

<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_trans_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Legal Cases - FCC v Pacifica (George Carlin `7 Dirty Words` Case)&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>ftp.eff.org, /pub/Legal/Cases/FCC_v_Pacifica
<br>gopher.eff.org, 1/Legal/Cases/FCC_v_Pacifica
<br>http://www.eff.org/pub/Legal/Cases/FCC_v_Pacifica/
</H5>



<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<H1><TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD></H1>
<H1><TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD></H1>
<H1><TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD></H1>
<H1><TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD></H1>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="fcc_v_pacifica.decision"><B>fcc_v_pacifica.decision</B></a>
<DD>Supreme Court decision in the 1974 George Carlin
    &quot;Seven Dirty Words&quot; case, FCC v. Pacifica Foundation (the original
    Carlin monologue that was the subject of the case was actually called
    &quot;Seven Words You Can Never Say on Television&quot;.) This decision established
    indecency regulation in broadcasting, and for over two decades has
    established the FCC as the largest censorship body in the world. This
    case is essentially one of the forebears of the &quot;Communications Decency
    Act&quot;.
</DL>

<br><hr><br>
