</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="tru_v_rru.summary"><B>tru_v_rru.summary</B></a>
<DD>Roadkills-R-Us author Miles O'Neal's summary
    of the Toys &quot;R&quot; Us legal threats and his responses to them.
<DT><a href="tru_042495.letter"><B>tru_042495.letter</B></a>
<DD>Toys &quot;R&quot; Us initial legal threat to author of
    Roadkills-R-Us.
<DT><a href="rru_050895.letter"><B>rru_050895.letter</B></a>
<DD>RRU's response to TRU's initial letter, explaining
    how absurd the threat is (RRU, as satire, is protected speech, not 
    trademark infringement, and RRU is not a legal entity of any kind,
    contrary to TRU misunderstanding that it is a company or corporation).
<DT><a href="tru_060995.letter"><B>tru_060995.letter</B></a>
<DD>second legal threat from TRU, again making ridiculous
    errors in supposing that RRU is some kind of commercial operation 
    despite being told otherwise.
<DT><a href="rru_062395.letter"><B>rru_062395.letter</B></a>
<DD>Second RRU response, outlining a &quot;happy ending&quot; and 
    even offering to help TRU get set up with a WWW site (they later did this
    by themselves)
<DT><a href="tru_090195.letter"><B>tru_090195.letter</B></a>
<DD>yet another threat letter to RRU.
<DT><a href="tru_101695.letter"><B>tru_101695.letter</B></a>
<DD>addendum to that letter. As usual, TRU still pretends
    RRU is a legal entity such as a corporation, infringing TRU trademarks.
<DT><a href="rru_110795.letter"><B>rru_110795.letter</B></a>
<DD>RRU letter to TRU warning against further harassment,
    and pointing out that RRU's name is constitutionally-protected expression.
    The letter also amusingly satirizes the stiff legalese of the TRU 
    attorneys
</DL>

