<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Jump</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<H2><CENTER>Jump</CENTER></H2>

Standing on the edge again sinking<BR>
thinking about watching the cliff slip by<BR>
and the sky, below<BR>
a familiar shade of sea green<BR>
<P>
I'll trade my life for a darker bit<BR>
of scenery without a promise<BR>
cause a promise, I promise is what I don't need<BR>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT10-B05-92</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA022-000241-B003-83</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://kragar.eff.org:80/~erict/Personal/Poetry/duck.html 204.253.162.4 19970108040046 text/html 979
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Wed, 08 Jan 1997 04:00:51 GMT
Server: Apache/1.1.1
Content-type: text/html
Content-length: 809
Last-modified: Wed, 11 Oct 1995 19:53:45 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<h3>Duck</H3><P>

When you die, I'll tell you what you'll be:
<br> when you die you'll be water
<br> water of the waterfalls, water of the boundless sea
<br> water of the clear stream that winds its
<br> way down uninhabited mountain valleys.
<br> grateful water from the skies
<br> soak the land wet after seven years of drought
<br> powerful water that rises
<br> above the shore and molds resolute cliffs to its whim
<br> water of tears-tears of joy at the unification of lost lovers
<p>
<br> when i die i'll be a bird:
<br> i'll not become a mournful cukoo,
<br> not even a bluebird on the tapestry of gems and fairies
<br> not a silver crane, nor a white gull
<br> i'll not even become a great eagle or falcon
<br> i shall become a duck
<br> a madarin duck 
<br> ever swimming on the green waters of you
</DOC>
<DOC>
