<H2><A NAME="dirs">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/filefolder_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40
ALT=""></A> Subdirectories in This Archive</H2>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF=".."><B>Up to the Parent Directory</B><P></a>
<DT><a href="Clipper/"><B>Clipper/</B></A>
<DD>Link to a directory pertaining to the Clipper Chip and
    electronic privacy issues; an extensive archive on these topics.
<DT><a href="Computer_security/"><B>Computer_security/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory pertaining to computer security 
    issues.
<DT><a href="Digital_money/"><B>Digital_money/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory pertaining to digital cash / digital 
    money issues (the electronic exchange of funds).
<DT><a href="Digital_signature/"><B>Digital_signature/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory which contains information on the 
    digital signature standard (DSS)
<DT><a href="RSA_v_NIST/"><B>RSA_v_NIST/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory with documents attacking NIST's adoption 
    of the DSS and the granting of patent rights to PKP. 
<DT><a href="Secure_Internet/"><B>Secure_Internet/</B></A>
<DD>Directory of info on IPNG, IPv6, IPSec, S/WAN, SHTTP, 
    TLS, Oakley, ISAKMP, SHTML, SSL, DNSS, Kerberos, and other Internet 
    privacy &amp; security efforts.
<DT><a href="Technical/"><B>Technical/</B></A>
<DD>
<DT><a href="Tools/"><B>Tools/</B></A>
<DD>Link to directory which contains information on cryptographic 
    tools and privacy programs.
</DL>

