<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="distance_health.summary"><B>distance_health.summary</B></a>
<DD>Paper by Arthur D. Little describing the health 
    care cost reductions that telemedicine would make possible by, among 
    other things, reducing unnecessary doctor and emergency room visits and 
    providing early diagnosis of many problems.
<DT><a href="fed_med_edu_agri_nii_funding.notices"><B>fed_med_edu_agri_nii_funding.notices</B></a>
<DD>pile of Federal govt. funding mechan-
    ism and grant notices re: agricultur al telecom, telemedicine, and
    distance learning. FY94
<DT><a href="health_uniserv_short.history"><B>health_uniserv_short.history</B></a>
<DD>A Short History of Universal Service:
    Progress of the Snowe-Rockefeller Amendment for providing Universal
    Services for 'Health Care Providers for Rural areas, Educational
    Providers, and Libraries', 1995
<DT><a href="med_training_online.article"><B>med_training_online.article</B></a>
<DD>Ron LaPorte's August 1994 article &quot;Towards
    Global Public Health Training through the Internet&quot; &quot;it is prime 
    time to establish a global training program in public health through 
    the capabilities that the internet provides and are enlisting 
    faculty and students to join this effort.&quot;
</DL>

