<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Eric Tachibana's Resume - Graduate Studies</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">

<H2><CENTER>Eric Tachibana's Resume - Graduate Studies</CENTER></H2>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

While attending The George Washington University's (GWU) Elliot School 
of International Affairs' Master's Program in Science, Technology and 
Public Policy I focussed primarily on the private and public sector 
management of information/telecommunications technology in a complex 
multinational marketplace.

<P>

My research included <A HREF = "../Prose/ip_in_info_era.html">Intellectual 
Property in the Information Era</A>, the web as an 
<A HREF = "../Prose/final.html" TARGET = "Resource Window">emergent 
system</A> as studied by Complexologists, <A HREF = 
"../Prose/privacy.html" TARGET = 
"Resource Window">digital privacy policy</A>, and the <A HREF = 
"../Prose/Complexity_threshold/" 
TARGET = "Resource Window">cultural ramifications of the Information 
Revolution</A>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
