<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="email.biblio"><B>email.biblio</B></a>
<DD>Erik Thelan's Jan 1989 bibliography of works on
    e-mail and other forms of electronic messaging and
    networked communications.
<DT><a href="gigabit_networking_paper.ps.gz"><B>gigabit_networking_paper.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>a PostScript-format article on how and why
    the advancement of networking technology to
    the gigabit-per-second speed level actually
    presents fewer problems and challenges than
    supposed initially in the 80s. This file is
    gzip-compressed.
<DT><a href="ip_speed_limits_paper.ps.gz"><B>ip_speed_limits_paper.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>a gzip-compressed PostScript-format speech
    transcript. Details the upper speed limits
    of TCP/IP networking, and where the bottle
    necks will be (not where you might think at
    first guess).
<DT><a href="net_economic.faq"><B>net_economic.faq</B></a>
<DD>This paper was prepared for the Tenth Michigan Public
    Utility Conference at Western Michigan University
    March 25--27, 1993. It describes the history, technology
    and cost structure of the Internet. We also describe a
    possible smart-market mechanism for pricing traffic on
    the Internet. Updated 11/14/93.
<DT><a href="net_economic.ps.gz"><B>net_economic.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>gzip-compressed PostScript version of net_economic.faq
    (see http://alfred.econ.lsa.umich.edu/FAQs/FAQs.html
    for WWW hypertext version).
<DT><a href="net_pricing_paper.ps.gz"><B>net_pricing_paper.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>This paper was prepared for the conference
    &quot;Public Access to the Internet&quot;, JFK School of
    Government, May 26--27 , 1993. It describes some
    of the technology and costs relevant to pricing
    access to the Internet and suggest a possible
    smart-market mechanism for pricing traffic on the
    Internet. Updated 11/14/93. gzip-compressed 
    PostScript file.
<DT><a href="pc_nfs_tcp-ip.faq"><B>pc_nfs_tcp-ip.faq</B></a>
<DD>Large FAQ covering personal computer Network File System
    and Internet Protocol applications and subjects (DOS
    and Mac.)
<DT><a href="tp-ix_intro.ps.gz"><B>tp-ix_intro.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>TP/IX protocol introduction. This is a gzip-compressed
    PostScript file.
<DT><a href="usenet_site.faq"><B>usenet_site.faq</B></a>
<DD>How to Become a Usenet Site
</DL>

