<h2><A NAME="offsite">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/earth2_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Links to Related Off-Site Resources</h2>
<DL>

<DT><B>INDEXES & SEARCH TOOLS/SERVICES</B>
<DD>NCSA's Internet Resources <A 
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/MetaIndex.html"> Meta-Index</A>
<DD>NCSA's Experimental <A 
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Demo/metaindex.html">Search Engine Meta-Index</A> (for WAIS, etc.; requires HTML forms support)
<DD>EINet <A HREF="http://galaxy.einet.net/galaxy.html">Galaxy</A> Guide 
to World-Wide Information and Services
<DD>O'Reilly's <A HREF="http://gnn.com/gnn/gnn.html">Global Network 
Navigator</A> (GNN)
<DD><A HREF="http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/prat/gridpoint/">Grid Point</A>, 
a good, concise "lauching pad" for WWW exploration
<DD><A HREF="http://www.cs.yale.edu/HTML/WorldWideWebTop.html">General 
Overview of Worldwide Internet Resources</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://acs2.bu.edu:3000/roses.cgi">Vampyr's Box of Roses</A>, 
a whimsical but recommendable jumping-off point for more net surfing
<DD><A HREF="http://netcenter.com">NetCenter</A> a hub-and-spokes model 
reciprocal linking system of WWW indexing.
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/global/home.html">Information 
Bank</A>'s collection of more than 700 links to Internet resources
<DD>General Information about the Internet - the <A 
HREF="http://www.lib.utk.edu:70/1/Other-Internet-Resources/General-Internet-Resources">Internet Assistance</A> Index
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/journalism/awesome.html">Awesome 
List</A>, John Makulowich's index of "the glory and grandeur of the Internet, the sine qua non of Cyberspace"
<DD><a href="http://netlink.wlu.edu:1020/">Netlink Server</a> - an index 
of gopher, telnet and WWW sites
<DD><A 
HREF="http://www.picosof.com:8080/html/scott.html">NetBook/ScottList</A>, an Internet site index, several thousand entries.
<DD><A HREF="http://kebono.stanford.edu/yahoo">Yahoo</A>, the Stanford 
index of WWW servers and resources (over <I>25,000</I> links!)
<DD><A HREF="http://www.mckinley.com/">McKinley WWW Search Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu/">CMU's Lycos WWW Search Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.infoseek.com/Home/">InfoSeek WWW Search Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.opentext.com:8080/">Open Text WWW Search Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://webcrawler.com/">WebCrawler WWW Search Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.dejanews.com/">DejaNews Usenet Archive Search 
Engine</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.excite.com/">Excite WWW & Usenet Search Engine, + Web
Site Reviews</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://Web.nexor.co.uk/susi/cusi.html">CUSI (CONFIGURABLE 
UNIFIED SEARCH INTERFACE)</A> - one interface for multiple WWW search engines
<DD><A HREF="http://cuiwww.unige.ch/meta-index.html">WWW Search Engine 
Meta-Index</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.excite.com">Excite</A> - yet another Internet search 
tool, but considered one of the better ones. Has the odd quirk that 
repeating the same search often yields widely divergent results.
<DD><A HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/netservices.html">Internet Resources 
List</A> WWW Server
<DD><A HREF="gopher://unix5.nysed.gov/">NYSEd</A>'s Gopher Index of 
Internet Resources and Happenings - the motherlode!
<DD><A HREF="http://twinbrook.cis.uab.edu:70/webNews.80">WebNews</A> an 
index of new WWW sites, created from scanning announcements posted to Usenet.
<DD><A HREF="http://www.mid.net/ARCHIVE">comp.archives</A> index - a 
"multi-field searchable database" of software announcements.
<DD>Search World-wide ftp Servers Using <A 
HREF="gopher://gopher.uiuc.edu:7999/7"> Archie</A> Search Tool
<DD>Search World-wide Gopher Servers Using <A 
HREF="gopher://veronica.scs.unr.edu:70/11/veronica"> Veronica</A> Search Tool
<DD>Directory of Wide-Area Information Service (<A 
HREF="gopher://gopher.nih.gov:70/11/tun/wais">WAIS</A>) Servers
<DD>World-wide<A 
HREF="gopher://gopher.tc.umn.edu:70/11/Other%20Gopher%20and%20Information%20Servers"> Gopher & Information Servers</A>
<DD>U. Minn. <A HREF="telnet://netfind@mudhoney.micro.umn.edu:0"> 
Netfind</A> Internet E-Mail Addresses Telnet Server
<DD>Search a massive index of <A HREF="http://sunsite.nus.sg/bibdb/bibdb.html">CD-ROM reasearch databases at SunSite</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/usenet-i/">SunSite Usenet Info
Center Launch Pad</A>
<DD>Searchable index of the <A 
HREF="http://criticalmass.com/concord/">comp.infosystems.* newsgroups</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.infi.net/cool.html">Cool Site of the Day</A>
<DD>Info on <A HREF="http://town.hall.org/brokers/Home.html">Harvest</A>, 
a new net.tool that provides flexible structured data arrangement & searching via WWW
<DD><A HREF="http://harvest.cs.colorado.edu/">Harvest demo and archive</A>
<DD>Online & Offline Publication <A HREF="http://www.mag-browse.com">Table 
of Contents</A> Server
<DD><A HREF="http://www.four11.com/">Four11: The Internet White Pages</A>
 - lists online people in a phonebook-like database
<DD>A <A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/~nlnnet/yellowp.html">"Yellow Pages"</A>
index of professional media/news websites, email addresses & more
<DD><A HREF="http://www.isoc.org/~bgreene/nsp-index.html">Internet Society's
Internet Service Provider List</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.best.be/iap.html">NetAccess Worldwide</A> - a 
large list of internet service providers.
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.nw.com/zone/WWW/top.html">Internet Domain
Survey</A> WWW Archive
<DD>Index of <A
HREF="http://www.mit.edu:8001/people/cdemello/univ.html">Academic
Internet Servers</A>
<DD>Another index of <A
HREF="http://akebono.stanford.edu/yahoo/Education/Universities/">academic
 Internet servers</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.petersons.com/">Internet Education Center</A>,
an archive of educational information online
<DD><A HREF="http://cspace.unb.ca/c-edres/">C-EdRes</A>, an index of
education-related Internet resources
<DD>The <A
HREF="http://www.openmarket.com/info/internet-index/">Internet Index</A>
- a WWW publication of Internet statistical information
<DD>Topical <A
HREF="gopher://una.hh.lib.umich.edu:70/11/inetdirsstacks/">Internet
Resource Guides</A> (about 100 of them!)
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.automatrix.com/conferences/">Internet
Conference Calendar</A>
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.columbia.edu/~hauben/index.html">Netizen's
Cyberstop</A> - info on net culture and history
<DD>The <A HREF="http://www.mid.net/net">Net Happenings Archive</A> (an
index of net-related news, incl. the creation of new mailing lists,
archive sites, etc.)

<DT><B>OTHER NET INFO, SERVICES &amp; TOOLS</B>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.irsociety.com/webchat.html">WebChat demo & 
archive</A> (WebChat is a realtime chat utility for WWW browsers)
<DD><A HREF="http://www.unipress.com/weblint/">WebLint</A>, an HTML syntax 
checker (upload HTML to it, or point it at a URL)
<DD><A HREF="http://oak.zilker.net">Alex</A>, an NSF-like method of 
treating FTP sites as part of one's own directory tree - neat tool!
<DD>The Internet Phone Company (tpc.int) Free <A 
HREF="http://town.hall.org/fax/faxsend-short.html">Fax-via-Internet</A> Service
<DD><A HREF="http://www.hw.ac.uk:8080/libWWW/irn/irn.html"><I>Internet 
Resources Newsletter</I> on the WWW</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.dis.org/fax/faxsend.html">Free WWW -> Fax Gateway</A>
<DD><A HREF="http://www.ffg.com/">WebWhacker</A> - Innovative tool to 
save locally a copy of any WWW page you find, and it even modifies the 
HTML codes to point to local copies of inlined graphics, etc.  You can, 
for example, use this to save a copy of your favorite EFFWeb page, 
complete with Icons, to load at start up quickly, w/o having to load the 
page from our server all the way across the net every time. Shareware.
<DD>Pacific System Group's <A
HREF="gopher://rain.psg.com:70/11/networks/">Network Information</A>
Gopher Archive - massive amount of material on Internet, BITNET,
FidoNet, X.400, Radio-based Networking, UUCP, Usenet, etc.; incl.
hard-to-find global info
<DD>Web Communications' <I>Comprehensive Guide to <A
HREF="http://www.webcom.com/html/">Publishing on the Web</A></I>
<DD><I><A HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/www.guide/">Entering the
World-Wide Web: A Guide to Cyberspace</A></I>
<DD><A HREF="file://weber.ucsd.edu/pub/usenet.hist">Internet/Usenet
History</A> FTP Site
<DD>Internet Network Information Center (<A
