<DD>proposed amendments to MD state bill hb1627.
<DT><a href="md_hb1627_94.article"><B>md_hb1627_94.article</B></a>
<DD>article discussing the failure of the Maryland Telecom
    Privacy Bill to pass committee markup in Feb of 1994. 
    Sponsored by MD House Delegate Joan Pitkin, bill HB1627 had
    several landmark provisions for consumer privacy protection.
<DT><a href="md_hb1627_94.bill"><B>md_hb1627_94.bill</B></a>
<DD>The actual text of the Maryland Telecom Privacy Bill of
    1994. House Bill HB1627, Sponsored by Del. Joan Pitkin. Bill died 
    in committee, Mar. 24, 1994, unfortunately, mainly due to lack of 
    citizen activism to show support, counteract negative commentary from 
    telco and cableco reps, and educate less clueful members of the committee.
</DL>

