<h2><A NAME="offsite">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/earth2_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Links to Related Off-Site Resources</h2>
<DL>

<DT><A 
HREF="http://www.ai.mit.edu/people/ellens/non.html"><B>Index</B></A> of
    Non-Profit Organizations on the Net
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.house.gov/white/internet_caucus/netcauc.html">The
Congressional Internet Caucus</A></B>
<DD>A new group of US legislators trying to protect the Internet
<DT>The MIT <A HREF="http://edf.www.media.mit.edu/">Electronic Democracy
    Forum</A>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.peak.org/vote-smart/">Project Vote Smart</A></B>
    <DD>Vote tallies, campaign finance info, and other details about US
    legislators).
<DT><B><A HREF="http://netvote96.mci.com/">Register to vote, online!</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.emf.net/~cr/pacdb.html">PAC contributions
database</A></B>
    <DD>Search for information on special interest group "political action
    committee" contributions to legislators
<DT><A href="http://www.mcs.net/~bkmurph/girvies.htm"><B>Girvies Davis'
    Homepage</B></A>
    <DD>"We got the victory" was the message that Girvies left
    for Chicago Tribune columnist Eric Zorn less than three hours before
    being executed. Governor Edgar rejected Girvies' Petition for
    Executive Clemency shortly before 5:00 p.m. on May 16, 1995. Girvies'
    Homepage discusses the use of the Internet in his struggles.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.copi.com/deepbook.htm">Deep Politics</A></B>
    <DD>online political books (corruption of democracy, govt. coverup, etc.)
<DT><A HREF="http://www.berkshire.net/~ifas/activist/"><B>Electronic
Activist</B></A>
  <DD>A state-by-state directory of U.S. congressmen, state legislators, and
   sundry media who have email addresses.
<DT><A HREF="http://lwvia.cornell-iowa.edu/Iowa/LSB/Lobbying/TOC.html">
 <B>Citizens' Guide to Lobbying</B></A>
 <DD>(by the Iowa Legislative Information Office)
<DT><B>Progressive Networks' <A HREF="http://www.wnia.org/wnia">What's 
New in Activism Online</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.xmission.com/~insearch/washington.html">'Mr.
Smith E-Mails Washington'</A></B>
<DD>A www form -> email-to-Congress gateway.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www2.portal.ca/~comprev/list.html">Vancouver 
Progressive Homepages Clearinghouse</A>
<DD>A list of activist links (as the name suggests, it leans toward middle 
and left causes, no right-wing representation from what this reviewer can 
see), divided into categories.  You can also get the list in <A 
HREF="http://www2.portal.ca/~comprev/webkit.html">hotlist/bookmarks 
form</A> for easy integration into Netscape, Explorer, etc.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.interactivism.com/">InterActivism</A></B>
<DD>A site which features several activism opportunities you can take 
part in at any given time. Has a "liberal" as well as a libertarian bent.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://policy.net/capweb/casey/hill/"><I>The Hill on the
Net </I></A></B>
<DD>Info on Chris Casey's new book about the US Congress coming into the 
information age.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.contact.org/sample/dir.htm">Contact Center
Network's Index of International Organizations</A></B>
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.contact.org/beta.html">Contact Center Network's
<I>Idealist </I></A></B>
<DD>the Interactive Clearinghouse of Nonprofit Services, Volunteer 
Opportunities, Jobs, Internships, Material and Events
<DT><B><A HREF="http://www.contact.org/tools/tools.htm">Contact Center Network's
Tools for Nonprofits and Community Organizations</A>
<DD>Index of the some of the best online resources for NGOs.
<DT><B><A HREF="http://vmag.law.vill.edu">Villanova Law School Center for
Information Law &amp; Policy</A></B>
<DD>Provides links to virtual arbitration experiment, government info
locators, & other legal resources.
<DT><A HREF="http://www.privacy.org/pi/activities/idcard/">Privacy
International's material on how to fight the implementation of national
ID card schemes
<DD>Draws on direct experience fighting Big Brother ID systems in
democracies to near-dicatorships, ranging from Australia, New Zealand, the
Phillipines, Thailand, and other countries.
<DT><A 
HREF="http://www.webactive.com/webactive/features/tips.html">Technology 
Tip Sheets for Nonprofits 
<DD>How-to for techies with a cause
</DL>

