<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_white_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Legislation - Oregon - Old/Historical&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>sb499.bill - Oregon Senate bill SB499; *incomplete* text; will post full text
<br> when obtained. may 25 1993.
<br>sb499_sb500.notes - Notes on 2 failed Oregon bills, SB499 and SB500, concerned
<br> with public access to govt. information. SB 500 took
<br> nearly 300 exemptions which currently exist in
<br> statute and consolidated them into fifteen categories of
<br> records to which an exemption from disclosure may
<br> apply. The bill outlines explicit balancing tests that
<br> apply to all exemptions except for those to which federal
<br> law mandates nondisclosure. SB 500 defines &quot;custodian&quot;,
<br> tightens the definition of public records, and provides
<br> for the continued use of ORS 192 for exemptions to
<br> disclosure.
<br> The companion, SB 499, provides for consistent treatment
<br> of disciplinary records of licensing boards for all
<br> professions. This bill specifically responded to
<br> significant disparities in how differently the release of
<br> disciplinary records were handles for different
<br> licensees. SB 499 cross references to SB 500 for
<br> guidelines on exemptions from disclosure.
<br> These notes go back quite a ways, and consist of reports,
<br> minutes of council sessions, etc. April 1994
<br>sb499_sb500_notes.sit.hqx - non-ASCII notes (charts, etc.) on the above, in
<br> misc. Mac formats (Excell, WP, etc.)
<br>sb500.bill - Oregon Senate bill SB500. *Incomplete* text, will post full text
<br> when available.
<br>sb500_fiscal.analysis - Legislative fiscal analysis of SB500 from April 1993.
<br>
</H5>



<h6>Last Updated Tue Jun 11 16:42:23 PDT 1996</h6><br>
