<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Review of Selena Sol's Scripts Archive in /MSGS From the 40s</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">

This copy is taken from the 
<A HREF = "http://www.tdl.com/~tuna/news/wwww.html">original</A> at 
<A HREF = "http://www.tdl.com/~tuna/news/index.html">/MSGS From the 40s</A>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Selena Sol's CGI script archive is a wonderful resource for those of you
wanting to do advanced HTML work, and totally useless to those of you that
dont. She has provided, free of charge, many CGI scripts which she has
authored, as well as some scripts from others, and a host of links. Not
only is Selena a talented programmer, but her graphic design is top notch.
Her page design is clean and functional, if somewhat understated. 
<P>
A quick techno-geek note for those who have no idea at all what I am
talking about... when you see a Web page with a form that accepts your
data and does something with it, like mailing it, or putting it in a guest
book, or when you follow a random link, there is something called a CGI
(Common Gateway Interface) script that makes all of this happen. 
Typically written in more-or-less cryptic languages such as C, PERL or
shell, these scripts are difficult to write. Selena has provided some very
powerful scripts here for all of us to use.  Thank you, Selena. 

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
