    February 26, 1994, entitled &quot;Clipper Chip: Government Monopoly in the 
    Making or Ineffective Law Enforcement.&quot; Lewis outlines the 
    government's Escrowed Encryption Standard (EES) and its pitfalls. 
<DT><a href="lp_v_clipper_digtel.announce"><B>lp_v_clipper_digtel.announce</B></a>
<DD>File containing Libertarian Party press 
    release, dated April 18, 1994, opposing the Digital Telephony and 
    Communications Act of 1994, calling it a serious infringement of civil 
