<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="nl_crypto.proposal"><B>nl_crypto.proposal</B></a>
<DD>A draft proposal to outlaw some forms of
    encryption, require licenses to use crypto, and escrow
    all crypto keys with the govt., in the Netherlands.
    The proposal also outrageously aims to extend
    Holland's jurisdiction to include those outside the
    country who &quot;import&quot; crypto via electronic means,
    such as mailing crypto software to people in Holland.
    File includes the proposal draft, and commentary.
    April 1994
<DT><a href="nl_crypto_ban.alert"><B>nl_crypto_ban.alert</B></a>
<DD>alert about the above draft proposal.
<DT><a href="nl_monitoring.article"><B>nl_monitoring.article</B></a>
<DD>march 1994 article from 'De Volkskrant' in English
    dealing with Directed tapping of mobile (cellular)
    phones...privacy v. law enforcement.
</DL>

